title: Charlie Rouse quintet TAKIN' CARE OF BUSINESS (1960)
description:
Best known as Monk's collaborator, Charlie Rouse's music is well able to stand

on it's own merits.  Rouse has a thick, distinctive tone and a bag full of

licks all his own.  Blue Mitchell adds solos and harmony on trumpet



JAZZLAND/OJC   11-MAY-1960



Charlie Rouse           TENOR

Blue Mitchell           TRUMPET

Walter Bishop           PIANO

Earl May                BASS

Art Taylor              DRUMS




track #2 "204" sounds much like another Randy Weston tune which became a 

jazz standard: HIGH FLY
